TEXT.Text:
{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Clear Canyon of Oblivion[Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Canyon of Oblivion - Wookiboki

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You need to check on Kunka to see if he is out of control. He may have lost it after learning of Sanka's plight. To check on Kunka, go to {C=0xFFFF5917}Canyon of Oblivion[Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Eradicate the wolves around town!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Giant wolves are attacking people around Odelia, part of the continent of Elyades!
Let's eradicate those wolves!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find traces of Lylia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Windia Plains - Rescue Agent John 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You must go to {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find {C=0xFF016295/}Traces of Lylia{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, the town chief's daughter.
There might be some monsters that are carrying some traces of her. Let's eradicate them and find out.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Alvin in Odelia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Alvin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traces of Lylia have been found, but we don't know where she is yet.
We may need to find Lylia through the use of Sorcery, but first lets go to  Alvin, his dog might be able to find something using the scent on this evidence.
The necklace has been sent to Alvin already, so the only thing left to do is go and meet Alvin to see what he found.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
We don't know what the reason is behind Lylia's kidnapping but we've found out where she is. Before we can rescue her, we need to meet Dun Morgan and ask for his permission.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Vagabond in Windia Plains [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Lylia's disappearance has something to do with the wolves' lair.
It may be too dangerous to go there alone, so let's do what the town chief suggested - clear the way in {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains Mission [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} first, and then go back and see him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Let's eradicate Vagabond and save Lylia! Hero Mode(F5)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Vagabond - Dun Morgan and Lylia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
All evidence seems to suggest that Dun Morgan's daughter is in the wolves lair.
There have been some reliable rumours that there is some kind of {C=0xFF016295/}Giant Wolf{C=0xFF4D0D08/} that has been seen around there.
It must be the wolf that's behind all this.
Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Vagabond{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains Mission Map [Hero Mode F5]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak to Alvin 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Reclusive Old Man, Alvin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dun Morgan says {C=0xFF016295/}Alvin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} should have helpful information about the town area.
Let's see what he knows.

Alvin is usually around {C=0xFF016295/}Odelia{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Also, it seems like Morgan left a{C=0xFFFF0000/} book{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for you. Check it in your {C=0xFFFF0000/}Inventory - Shop tab{C=0xFF4D0D08/} once you get it.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
1 Smelly Wolf Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Advanced Windia Plains - Parker

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
After the Wolf hunt in Windia Plains was successful, the movements then concentrated towards {C=0xFF016295/}Advanced Windia Plains{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
There must be a leader of the pack.
There might also be some connection to that suspicious doctor.
Hunting a {C=0xFF016295/}Ember Wolf{C=0xFF4D0D08/} should produce a {C=0xFF016295/}Smelly Wolf's claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/} You can find them in {C=0xFF016295/}Advanced Windia Plains{C=0xFF016295/}[Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Clear Vegas at Windia Plains Mission Arcade Mode F1

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Advanced Windia Plains - Parker

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
While Parker analyses the Wolf Claw, eliminate the wolves that wander around the four roads of {C=0xFF016295/}Advaned Windia Plains [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Parker doesn't want you to be bored while he's analysing the Wolf Claw you brought to him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Eradicate Vegas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Another wolf lair has been discovered aside from the one in Windia Plains.

Parker would like you to check out the Wolves Lair location in {C=0xFF016295/}Advanced Windia Plains [Hero Quest Mode F5]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find the wounded guard  - Traitors Ridge

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Wounded guard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
There is a {C=0xFF016295/}Wounded Guard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFF016295/}located in Traitor's Ridge{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Find him and listen to what happened.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Give 5 waters to the wounded Guard, Mette

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Wounded Guard, Mette

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You found {C=0xFF016295/}wounded guard Mette{C=0xFF4D0D08/} around {C=0xFF016295/}Traitor's Ridge{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.  His condition appears to be bad. To help him, give him 5 waters. You can get waters from monsters in Traitor's Ridge. Mette is going to give you something good as a reward!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Mercenary Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Mercenary Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Let's find out more details about the Udaka bandits by talking to {C=0xFF016295/}Thomas at Traitor's Ridge{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 10 Raccoons, 10 Plunger Raccoons and 10 Scrappies

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Mercenary Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 10 Raccoons, 10 Changos and 10 Scrappies while Thomas is checking the perimeter.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge [Arcade Mode(F1)] - Slay 5 monsters around Boss Sanka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Mercenary Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas has found out that there are even more dangerous monsters lurking deep in Traitor's Ridge [Arcade Mode(F1)].
Let's go slay {C=0xFF016295/}5 monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} around  {C=0xFF016295/}Boss Sanka in Traitor's Ridge [Arcade Mode(F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Dun Morgan in Odellia.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odellia - Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to Thomas, he hasn't seen any tourists these days. He thought that it was bandits, but now he's not so sure, as the banits are far from that road. So he is worried about Odelia. Therefore he asked me to meet  {C=0xFF016295/}Dun Morgan{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Odelia{C=0xFF4D0D08/}by using {C=0xFF016295/}Odelia Return Scroll{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Equipment Merchant Billy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Equipment Merchant Billy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
After the heroes left, monsters appeared in the Odelia and tourists are coming back from Port of the Winds. Town Chief Dun Morgan wanted to know about it a little more, so he requested that we collect some information from {C=0xFF016295/}Equipment Merchant Billy{C=0xFF4D0D08/}anything that he heard from tourists.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Innkeeper Florence

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Innkeeper Florence

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Equipment Merchant Billy said that there might be a lot of guests and tourists in the Inn. So suggested we meet {C=0xFF016295/}Innkeeper Florence{C=0xFF4D0D08/} after that.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Town Chief Don Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Town Chief Don Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Innkeeper Florence heard the tourist's saying that most of the tourists got attacked by {C=0xFF016295/}a couple of wolves{C=0xFF4D0D08/}and the place where they got attacked is Traitor's Ridge. Let's take this information to Town Chief Dun Morgan.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Thomas in the Traitor's Ridge.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dun Morgan said that Thomas has better knowledge about Traitor's Ridge. So he wanted to pass this information to {C=0xFF016295/}Thomas{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Traitor's Ridge{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Let's use the Warp Tower and get to Thomas in the Traitor's Ridge without delay.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Guppy in the Traitor's Ridge

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Guppy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas said that maybe Guppy saw something so we need to ask {C=0xFF016295/}Guppy{C=0xFF4D0D08/} if he saw wolves or not.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Getting Worn-out Novel from Axel and Chango in the Traitor's Ridge.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Guppy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Guppy lost his precious novel last night. According to him, {C=0xFF016295/}Axel and Chango{C=0xFF4D0D08/} are his prime suspects for the novel so let's go to them and get back Guppy's {C=0xFF016295/}Worn-out Novel{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Patrolling over Howling Wind's Hill

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Howling Wind's Hill - ??????

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
I told Guppy's story to Thomas. Thomas was surprised and he's worried about the isolation of Odelia. Let's enter {C=0xFF016295/}Howling Wind's Hill{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find the Wolves' Den!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter the Wolves' Den and slay the monster.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Howling Wind's Hill - Keion

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
I met wounded Keion at the Howling Wind's Hill. He tried to go Port of the Winds from Odelia but he got wonded from a sudden attack from a monster. That monster should be the one which tried to attack the tourists at the Traitor's Ridge! Let's go to {C=0xFF016295/}Wolves' Den{C=0xFF4D0D08/}and slay that monster!!!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Thomas in Traitor's Ridge.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The thing in the Wolves' Den should be reported to {C=0xFF016295/}Thomas{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Traitor's Ridge{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. The wounded tourist's status is unstable so let's go to Traitor's Ridge ASAP.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Report to Dun Morgan in the Odelia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas asked {C=0xFF016295/}Dun Morgan{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Odelia{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to enhance the security level and keep them up to date on the situation

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Give Dun Morgan's thanks to Thomas in the Traitor's Ridge.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dun Morgan wants to give his thanks to {C=0xFF016295/}Thomas{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the Traitor's Ridge. At this time, do not walk to Traitor's Ridge, just use {C=0xFF016295/}Warp Tower{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and go there directly!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get Sanka's Horn Flute at Traitor's Ridge - Arcade Mode F1

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Mercenary Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It was Sanka's Horn Flute that was causing all the monsters to attack the town. We need to enter the Arcade Mode F1, slay Sanka, and return with the Horn Flute!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter Traitor's Ridge [Arcade Mode(F1)] Normal(F2) or Hard(F3) and get Sanka's Horned Flutes.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Mercenary Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
There's more than one Sanka! Complete {C=0xFF016295/} Traitor's Ridge[Arcade Mode(F1)] {C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFF016295/}Normal(F2){C=0xFF4D0D08/} or {C=0xFF016295/}Hard(F3){C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect {C=0xFF016295/}2{C=0xFF4D0D08/}  {C=0xFF016295/}Sankas' Horned Flutes{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge Scenario Mode F5 - Defeat Sanka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge Scenario Mode F5 - Sanka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The way to the real Kunka has been opened.
You must defeat Sanka in order to save a real Kunka.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Search for Thomas!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mercenary Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
In order to save Kunka, you must get {C=0xFF016295/}Sanka's Disguise Mask{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFF016295/}Thomas{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

Let's look for Thomas at the {C=0xFF016295/}Watch tower at Traitor's Ridge Mission [Mission Mode]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Canyon of Oblivion - Meet Kunka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Canyon of Oblivion - Kunka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat {C=0xFF016295/}Kunka, the ruler of the Canyon of Oblivion mission map{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Perhaps beating him might provide an answer to why they lost their minds and attacked everyone.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Canyon of Oblivion [Arcade Mode(F1)]Hard(F3)- Obtain Sanka Disguise Scroll

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Canyon of Oblivion - Wookiboki

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Wookiboki told you how to get into Kunkah's Cave! 
Get Sanka Disguise Scroll from {C=0xFF016295/} Canyon of Oblivion[Arcade Mode(F1)] Hard(F3){C=0xFF4D0D08/} and come Back to Wookiboki. (Wookiboki is not very clear to understand, let's just get the point. OK?)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Entering Hero Mode as camouflage like Sanka. (Attack  is prohibited)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Canyon of Oblivion - Wookiboki 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Wear the camouflage as Sanka and infiltrate into Kunka's hideout and get the real Kunka on their knees! If you attack any monster, you will not be enter into the mission mode map of Hero's quest so don't attack any monsters in there. If your camouflage broken, visit Wookiboki again and camouflage as Sanka again.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Let's meet Colin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Guard Captain Colin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kunka can't remember anything except for this woman that he described ambiguously.
Let's meet {C=0xFF016295/}Colin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and see what he has to say.
Colin can be found in {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Odelia's town chief Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Wolves have been attacking the town recently. The town chief's daughter has been kidnapped by these wolves and it seems that they are being controlled by someone. Let's talk to the town chief {C=0xFF016295/}Dun Morgan{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 7 Ash Wolves

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Thief Jack

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
We need to slay {C=0xFF016295/}7 Ash Wolves{C=0xFF4D0D08/} then inform {C=0xFF016295/}Jack in Odelia{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Windia Plains Arcade Mode F1 - Achieve Rank C in 2 Maps

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Thief Jack 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jack the thief has made a bet with you.
{C=0xFF016295/}Achieve at least Rank C in Windia Plains Mission Map [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and he'll give you a good reward.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Advanced Windia Plains Mission Map [Arcade Mode F1] Achieve Rank B

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Thief Jack 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thief Jack has made a bet with you.
{C=0xFF016295/}Achieve Rank B or higher in Advanced Windia Plains Mission Map [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Thief Jeff at Traitor's Ridge

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Thief Jeff

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jack in Odelia wants you to deliver this letter to his brother Jeff at Traitor's Ridge. This looks suspicious. We've already promised to deliver the letter though, so just play along.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find treasure chest at Traitor's Ridge

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Thief Jeff

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The thief brothers want to find the treasure chest in Traitor's Ridge Mission Map (3 Stars). Find it and deliver it to Jeff!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find the Treasure Chest at Bearded Whale Coast Arcade Mode F1

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Thief Jeff

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter Bearded Whale Coast Arcade Mode F1 and find the treasure chest. Deliver it to Jeff afterwards.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find the Treasure Chest at the Sanctuaries Arcade Mode F1

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Thief Jeff

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter the Sanctuaries Arcade Mode F1 and find a treasure chest. Deliver it to Jeff afterwards.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 5 Plain Wood from Woodies in Windia Plains [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Guard Captain Dustin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 5 Plain Wood for the festival as required by Captain Dustin in Odelia.
{C=0xFFFF5917/}Plain Wood{C=0xFF4D0D08/} can been found on {C=0xFFFF5917/}Woodies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains Mission Map [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

You can access Mission Maps at the Padlock Symbol on the Minimap in most field map areas.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 5 Horned Skulls at Windia Plains

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Guard Captain Dustin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 5 Horned Skulls for the festival as required by Captain Dustin. You can get Horned skulls from {C=0xFF016295/} Rams in Windia Plains{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 7 Brown Wolves

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Guard Captain Dustin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}Guard Captain Dustin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} wants you to kill {C=0xFF016295/}7 Brown Wolves at Windia Plains{C=0xFF4D0D08/} as vengeance for injuring him the last time.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}10 Easter Eggs with Rabbit Drawings {C=0xFF4D0D08/} - From all {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Maps [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}15 Easter Eggs{C=0xFF4D0D08/} - Given on Log in

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Event Manager Gato{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Event Manager Gato{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is giving out a present to all users for Easter, an {C=0xFF016295/}[Easter Achievement]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, but it's not easy to gain. {C=0xFFFF0000/}A Giant Rabbit{C=0xFF4D0D08/} will appear in every {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Map [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, defeat them and collect 10 {C=0xFF016295/}Easter Eggs with Rabbit Drawings{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and 15 {C=0xFF016295/}Easter Eggs{C=0xFF4D0D08/} given when you login.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}7 Easter Eggs with Rabbit Drawing{C=0xFF4D0D08/} - From all {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Map [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Event Manager Gato{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Gato{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is running low on eggs again. This time the
{C=0xFFFF0000/}Giant Rabbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/} have taken the villages eggs. Let's go and get then back from the{C=0xFFFF0000/}Giant Rabbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You can find them in any {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Map [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Shouldn't Gato be doing this??

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}7 Easter Egg with Rabbit Drawing{C=0xFF4D0D08/} - From all {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Map [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Event Manager Gato{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
We are still running short on eggs. {C=0xFFFF0000/}Giant Rabbit's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} have hidden more eggs. Let's go and get more eggs from the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Giant Rabbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You can find {C=0xFFFF0000/}Giant Rabbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in any {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Map [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}7 Easter Egg with Rabbit Drawing{C=0xFF4D0D08/} - From all {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Map [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Event Manager Gato{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Event Manager Gato{C=0xFF4D0D08/} gave too many eggs out, and they are running short again!
The {C=0xFFFF0000/}Giant Rabbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/} have hidden more eggs. Let's go and get more eggs from the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Giant Rabbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You can find them in any {C=0xFF00863C/}Mission Map [Arcade Mode (F4)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Shouldn't Gato be doing this??

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get an apple and give it to Boatman Zaza

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Traitor's Ridge - Boatman Zaza

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find one {C=0xFF016295/}Apple{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Boatman Zaza{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
You'll get apples from monsters in {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 5 Fleeces

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Boatman Zaza

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}Zaza{C=0xFF4D0D08/} wants Fleece in exchange for information. You can get fleeces at Windia Plains.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 5 Woodies

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Guard Oliver

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You happened to meet your old friend Oliver.
He said he can give you some information, but for a price.
Dispatch {C=0xFF016295/}5 Woodies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in Windia Plains in exchange for information.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 7 Brown Wolves

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Guard Oliver

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay {C=0xFF016295/}7 Brown Wolves{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at Windia Plains as requested.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 5 Woodies

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mystia Lane - Arcanist Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pablo has prepared 3 tests for people who wish to become like him. 
First test is to slay 5 Woodies in Windia Plains.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get a Parchment

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mystia Lane - Arcanist Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Second test is a test of wisdom. Work your wits to obtain Papyrus. Speak to the townsfolk.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 5 Rams

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Arcanist Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Third test is to test one's will. Go to Windia Plains and slay 5 Rams!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Windia Plains - Get 7 Spider Poisons

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mystia Lane - Arcanist Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The last test is about the chosen path. You must slay Spees and Spikes to collect their poison.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 5 Firewood for Pamela

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Wine Merchant Pamela

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring 5 Firewood to Pamela. Firewood can be obtained by slaying Woodies at Windia Plains.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get a piece of cake and give it to Adelio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Mercenary Adelio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Working with Adelio brings fortune.
To make more money, try to be nice to Adelio!
First, get cake from Heidi and give it to Adelio.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 5 Woodies

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Mercenary Adelio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to Adelio, Woodies are bothering people in Odelia. Defeat 5 Woodies at Windia Plains.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 5 Fleeces at Windia Plains

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Mercenary Adelio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 5 Fleece for Adelio in exchange for more information.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 7 Spider Poisons

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Mercenary Adelio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Adelio says that there's a demand for adhesive made from Spider Poison. Find 7 Spider Poisons for him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Guard Walter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Guard Walter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D09/}
Floranes son, Chuck, has vanished. File a missing persons report to Guard Walter who is in Port of the Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Talk to Innkeeper Florane.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Innkeeper Florane.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to Walter, Chuck was acting suspicious and heading somewhere with a small bag.
Inform Florane of this latest information.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Talk to Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To save Chuck, you should meet the detective.
His name is Gordon. You could see him at the Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Answer Detective Gordon's questions. 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Answer the Detective's questions to help him to investigate this mystery.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Finding an eye-witness (Talk Jeff in the Bearded Whale Coast for more info)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thief Jeff

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Try to find someone who saw Chuck before he went missing, start with Jeff in the Bearded Whale Coast.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Collect 20 empty boxes

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Sneaky Thief Jeff

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sneaky Thief Jeff is the one and only eye-witness to see Chuck. But there's no free lunch.()
Collect empty boxes from the monsters around Bearded Whale Coast. Bring those boxes to Sneaky Thief Jeff and he will let you know about Chuck.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Talk to Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to Jeff, He saw Chuck near the front of the Cookie Factory.
But Chuck disappeared very suddenly so Jeff wasn't able to talk with him. Update Detective Gordon with this new information.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Speak with Factory Manager Yamaki and try to enter the Cookie Factory. Return to Detective Gordon when finished.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
All of the kids who had an invitation are missing. For this reason, it must be a kidnapping so Detective Gordon wants you to get into the Cookie Factory and investigate what is going on in there. Talk to Yamaki to enter the Cookie Factory.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 20 cookie papers at the Jigsaw Pincers Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It seems the only way to get into the Cookie Factory is with an invitation.
Detective Gordon has agreed to forge an invitation for you but he needs some Cookie Papers to complete the forgery. 
Collect 20 cookie papers from the monsters at the Jigsaw Pincers Coast and give it to Detective Gordon.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter to Cookie Factory - Clear Difficulty Lv. 1

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Everything is ready. Let's enter the Cookie Factory and rescue those children!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter to Cookie Factory - Clear Difficulty Lv. 2 and 3

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The children were kidnapped but it gets worse;they've been turned into MONSTERS!
They are in great danger now. Enter the Cookie Factory Lv. 2 and 3 as soon as possible to rescue them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cookie Factory - Save Chuck (Clear Difficulty Lv. 4 )

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
We still haven't found Chuck yet. Enter into Lv. 4 continue the search for Chuck!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cookie Factory - Find a map of the Cookie Factory or some kind of Cookie Factory Floor-plan (Lv. 1~4)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
We still don't know who kidnapped the children and transformed them into monsters. Detective Gordon believes that a closer inspection of the Cookie Factory will provide some clue as to the possible location of the master criminal behind all this.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cookie Factory - Enter into Hidden Place (Clear Hero Mode(F5))

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
????? (Unknown)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
At last the secret lair has been revealed. Venture inside and discover the fiend behind all these monstrous events.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Speak with Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Derek confessed to causing all this trouble, in an effort to find a successor for the Cookie Factory.  Let's get out of the factory and let Gordon know about this news first.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cookie Factory - Arrest Derek (Clear Hero Mode (F5))

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Detective Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Re-enter the Cookie Factory Hero Mode, defeat Derek and bring him to justice!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cookie Factory – get 4 kinds of Valentine day balloons

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds – Yamaki

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}Yamaki{C=0xFF4D0D08/}who are yelling love and passion, tell me about the LOVE balloon story. {C=0xFF016295/}I've told if we make perfect word LOVE and have a party, we could get bonus EXP.{C=0xFF4D0D08/}  Let's get into the {C=0xFF016295/}Cookie Factory{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get the balloons.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind  - Talk to Haruka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind  - Haruka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Haruka is a girl who runs Haruka's Sushi Restaurant. She has managed her restaurant by using the big tea cup which is her house heritage. But a chef with a scary face came to Haruka's Sushi Restaurant and kicked her out to get the tea cup.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Haruka's Sushi Restaurant Mission Map in [Arcade Mode(F1)] - Get 5 Burnish iron wires, 8 Pieces of Intact Pendants, 12 Glittering Jewels, 20 Fresh Cherry Blossom Leaves.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind  - Haruka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Haruka said the key for the place was broken when she struggled with the chef. The key was made of Cherry Blossom. To make it again there are some ingredients needed. Obtain {C=0xFF016295/} 5 Burnish iron wires, 8 Pieces of Intact Pendants, 12 Glittering Jewels and 20 Fresh Cherry Blossom Leaves in [Arcade Mode(F1)] of Haruka's Sushi Restaurant {C=0xFF4D0D08/} and give them to Haruka. She'll make the necklace again.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Haruka's Sushi Restaurant Hero Mission - Defeat Steel Chef

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind  - Haruka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Now it's possible to gain entry and find Haruka's tea cup by using the Cherry Blossom pendant. However,  beware the chef who waits inside. Defeat the Steel Chef before he steals the item you seek!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 4 Secret Scrolls of Cherry Blossom in [Haruka's Sushi Restaurant Arcade mode (F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds Haruka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
