Spirit of Old Tree in Muddy Swamp must be existed only one in the same space. According to him, they will collapse if when they contact each other. I don't know well but I decided to take his request.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
10 Kentars' Hooves

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Injured Good Kentar Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
This was a holy place for Kentars originally.
But a traitorous evil Kentar took the land by force and started a cult.

Let's help the good Kentars reclaim their land.
Let's eradicate the evil {C=0xFF016295/}Kentar{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect {C=0xFF016295/}10 Kentar Hooves{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Eradicate 15 Kentars

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Injured Good Kentar Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You must buy some time for the Injured Good Kentar so that he can make a key.
Let's {C=0xFF016295/}Eradicate 15 Kentars{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Eradicate Karkarous - Scenario Mode F5

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Injured Good Kentar Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Finally a key is made to enter the place where {C=0xFF016295/}Karkarous{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is hiding.
Let's eradicate Karkarous and bring peace to the Kentars again.
The way to Karkarous can be found to the left of the injured Centaur  [Scenario Mode(F5)].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The lettering on the Stones show Paris and her role in the struggle between the Dragons and the Humans. It seems she is somehow connected to all this chaos and war. This must be reported to {C=0xFF016295/}Fungarf{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Finding humans in town

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Human merchant in town

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Arrived at the Fungoid village only to find out that you can't understand what they're saying.
Let's try and find {C=0xFF016295/}humans to speak with in the town{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Sanson the Blacksmith

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Sanson the Blacksmith

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Massenran says that {C=0xFF016295/}Sanson the Blacksmith{C=0xFF4D0D08/} was able to learn the Fungoid language very fast. Let's ask Sanson how he did it.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Camilla the Banker

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Camilla the Banker

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sanson says he was able to understand the Fungoid language right after he drank a potion that the Fungoid Chief, Fungarf, gave him.
However, he doesn't know much about it but he says that {C=0xFF016295/}Camilla the Banker{C=0xFF4D0D08/} does. Let's talk to her.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 50 Zards - Blizard Ridge

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Camilla the Banker

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Camilla knew about the secret of understanding the Fungoid language. 
But she says she'll only tell you if you help her.
She needs {C=0xFF016295/}50 Zards slain at Blizzards Ridge{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet High Magician Elsa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - High Magician Elsa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Camilla the Banker gave you the Shoontin Potion production manual.
The only person that can make the potion is High Magician Elsa. Let's show the {C=0xFF016295/}Shoontin Potion production manual {C=0xFF4D0D08/}to Elsa.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tutu Tree Forest - 25 Roots and 20 Big Leaves

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Elsa the High Magician

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Some plant materials are needed to make the Shoontin potion. And since no one has them, you have to get it yourself...
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Tutu Tree Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get {C=0xFF016295/}15 Roots and 20 Big Leaves from Evil Vine Flower and Evil Seed Flower{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Fungoid Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Now you understand their language!
Let's speak with {C=0xFF016295/}Chief Fungarf{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Cori the Gorilla

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Village of Slumber - Cori the Gorilla

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It seems that the {C=0xFF016295/}Gorillas that Chief Fungarf raised{C=0xFF4D0D08/} ran away from home when the chief couldn't afford to feed them. Head to the Village of Slumber and talk to the leader of the runaway Gorillas, {C=0xFF016295/}Cori{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Fairy Grania

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Frigid Canyon - Fairy Grania

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ringo recently found out that he had loved and married a fairy from the Land of Temptation and not a human. He ran away promptly but he's curious about how she's doing.
Let's meet {C=0xFF016295/}Grania the Fairy at Frigid Canyon{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tutu Tree Forest - Kill 40 Mimir

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Fungoid Mage Spooky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Spooky also says that he cannot trust humans because he thinks that humans have betrayed Fungoids and sided with Kentars.
Spooky demands you to kill {C=0xFF016295/}40 Mimirs{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, in the alley of Kentarous in {C=0xFF016295/}Tutu Tree Forest {C=0xFF4D0D08/} to prove that you could help him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Achieve a 200-hit combo in Gods' Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Completion NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Advanced Class manager

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get training from advanced class mangers in Fungoid Village. 
The first task would be perform a 200-hit combo on the monsters in {C=0xFF016295/}Tutu Tree Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You've delivered a letter from Fungarf, but the Gorillas can't read it.
Let's tell {C=0xFF016295/}Chief Fungarf{C=0xFF4D0D08/} about it.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Ringo in the Village of Ash Mist 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Ringo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Grania now regrets marrying Ringo, a human. Bring {C=0xFF016295/}Ringo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} the bad news.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Meet Chief Fungarf 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Completion NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
As a representative of Melanathos, you not only need to possess substantial combat skills, but have the benevolence to help others and keep the peace!
Let's speak to Chief Fungarf and let him know the goodwill of Man so that we can help Fungoid Village!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Cori the Gorilla

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Village of Slumber - Cori the Gorilla

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Let's meet {C=0xFF016295/}Cori the Gorilla{C=0xFF4D0D08/}again and tell him that it will be 4 acorns in the morning and 3 at night.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Fairy Grania

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Frigid Canyon - Fairy Grania

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ringo realizes that he was wrong and asked to deliver a letter for him to Grania the Fairy in the Frigid Canyon. 
Let's meet her again and give her the letter.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ocher Forest - Get 20 Dry Firewoods and Ancient Trees

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Completion NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Innkeeper Mosanra

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To regain Fungarf's faith, you have to help them to restore their destroyed village. First of all, to straighten up fallen houses, bring 20 firewood pieces and 20 Ancient trees. 
You will be able to find the items from the {C=0xFF016295/}Toenail Wing Kinsmen{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFF016295/}Toenail Wing Patrols{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Tutu Tree Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Gorillas say that they're sick of acorns and want bananas instead from now on.
Let's tell {C=0xFF016295/}Chief Fungarf{C=0xFF4D0D08/}about this.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get Snake Flower Cane from Arka in Frigid Canyon Mission Mode

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Frigid Canyon - Fairy Grania

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It turns out that Grania hasn't forgotten Ringo either. But since it is forbidden for Fairies to marry humans, she was imprisoned for 80 years. The only way to get out is to use the Snake Flower Cane the Arka holds.
Let's get the Snake Flower Cane from Arka!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tutu Tree Forest - 10 Sticky Yellow Fluid, 20 Sticky Brown Fluid

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - InnKeeper Mosanra

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Now you have to get 10 Sticky Yellow Fluid and 20 Sticky Brown Fluid to sticky buildings and woods. 
Sticky Fluids can be obtained from{C=0xFF016295/}Worm and Larva Rake{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Tutu Tree Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Return to Mosanra after getting all required materials.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Village of Slumber Scenario Mode (F5) - Burlune

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Village of Slumber - Cori the Gorilla

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay {C=0xFF016295/}Burlune{C=0xFF4D0D08/} deep within the Village of Slumber Scenario Mode F5 so that Fungarf's gorillas will come back.

